						Evermay Wealth Management LLC Has $444,000 Position in Enterprise Products Partners L.P. (NYSE:EPD)					

						 July 1st, 2017  - 0 comments - Filed Under -
 by Nicole Kennedy 


							Filed Under: Investing - SEC Filing Articles 






Tweet










Evermay Wealth Management LLC held its stake in shares of  Enterprise Products Partners L.P. (NYSE:EPD) during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The fund owned 16,095 shares of the oil and gas producer’s stock at the end of the first quarter. Evermay Wealth Management LLC’s holdings in Enterprise Products Partners L.P. were worth $444,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other large investors have also recently made changes to their positions in EPD. Heritage Wealth Advisors bought a new stake in  Enterprise Products Partners L.P. during the first quarter valued at approximately $1,892,000.  Hutner Capital Management Inc. boosted its stake in  Enterprise Products Partners L.P. by 3.5% in the first quarter. Hutner Capital Management Inc. now owns 83,149 shares of the oil and gas producer’s stock valued at $2,296,000 after buying an additional 2,840 shares in the last quarter.  GWM Advisors LLC boosted its stake in  Enterprise Products Partners L.P. by 6.6% in the first quarter. GWM Advisors LLC now owns 45,210 shares of the oil and gas producer’s stock valued at $1,247,000 after buying an additional 2,796 shares in the last quarter.  Chatham Capital Group Inc. boosted its stake in  Enterprise Products Partners L.P. by 1.4% in the first quarter. Chatham Capital Group Inc. now owns 127,523 shares of the oil and gas producer’s stock valued at $3,524,000 after buying an additional 1,764 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Peapack Gladstone Financial Corp boosted its stake in  Enterprise Products Partners L.P. by 94.2% in the first quarter. Peapack Gladstone Financial Corp now owns 29,741 shares of the oil and gas producer’s stock valued at $821,000 after buying an additional 14,425 shares in the last quarter. 38.56% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 
Shares of Enterprise Products Partners L.P. (EPD) opened at 27.08 on Friday. The company has a market capitalization of $57.85 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 21.93 and a beta of 0.91. Enterprise Products Partners L.P. has a 52 week low of $24.01 and a 52 week high of $30.25. The stock has a 50 day moving average of $26.79 and a 200-day moving average of $27.40. 




Enterprise Products Partners L.P. (NYSE:EPD) last announced its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 2nd. The oil and gas producer reported $0.36 EPS for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.32 by $0.04. The firm had revenue of $7.32 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $6.05 billion. Enterprise Products Partners L.P. had a net margin of 10.31% and a return on equity of 11.73%. Enterprise Products Partners L.P.’s revenue was up 46.3% on a year-over-year basis. During the same period last year, the firm posted $0.33 EPS.  On average, analysts anticipate that  Enterprise Products Partners L.P. will post $1.42 EPS for the current year. 
ILLEGAL ACTIVITY NOTICE: “Evermay Wealth Management LLC Has $444,000 Position in Enterprise Products Partners L.P. (NYSE:EPD)” was first  published by Watch List News and is the property of of Watch List News. If you are viewing this article on another site, it was illegally stolen and reposted in violation of US & international copyright laws. The legal version of this article can be viewed at https://www.watchlistnews.com/evermay-wealth-management-llc-has-444000-position-in-enterprise-products-partners-l-p-nyseepd/1406408.html. 
Several equities research analysts have recently commented on EPD shares. Scotiabank  reaffirmed a “buy” rating and issued a $33.00 target price on shares of Enterprise Products Partners L.P. in a research report on Sunday, March 12th. Macquarie  reaffirmed an “outperform” rating and issued a $32.00 target price on shares of Enterprise Products Partners L.P. in a research report on Friday, April 21st. Jefferies Group LLC  reaffirmed a “buy” rating and issued a $33.00 target price on shares of Enterprise Products Partners L.P. in a research report on Tuesday, April 4th. Guggenheim started coverage on shares of Enterprise Products Partners L.P. in a research report on Monday, April 17th. They issued a “buy” rating and a $32.00 target price for the company. Finally, BidaskClub raised shares of Enterprise Products Partners L.P. from a “strong sell” rating to a “sell” rating in a research report on Tuesday. One equities research analyst  has rated the stock with a sell rating, seventeen have issued  a buy rating and one  has issued  a strong buy rating to the company’s stock. The stock  has an average rating of “Buy” and an average target price of $32.00.
Enterprise Products Partners L.P. Company Profile
Enterprise Products Partners L.P. (Enterprise) is a provider of midstream energy services to producers and consumers of natural gas, natural gas liquids (NGLs), crude oil, petrochemicals and refined products in North America. The Company’s segments include NGL Pipelines & Services; Crude Oil Pipelines & Services; Natural Gas Pipelines & Services, and Petrochemical & Refined Products Services.
Want to see what other hedge funds are holding EPD? Visit HoldingsChannel.com to get the latest 13F filings and insider trades for Enterprise Products Partners L.P. (NYSE:EPD).



