Evermay Wealth Management LLC



 OVERVIEW



Date Founded


2008




Headquarters


1776 Wilson Boulevard, Suite 310, Arlington, VA 22209-2517




Employees (Worldwide)


9




Industries


Investment Services & Portfolio Management




Company Description


Evermay Wealth Management employs a long-term asset allocation strategy that emphasizes diversification and discipline over market timing. Through their open architecture investment platform, the firm conducts a rigorous process for selecting managers focusing only on the most consistent and best performing. Equity and fixed-income investments are selected their potential to enhance portfolio performance.  Evermay uses sophisticated optimization and allocation models to identify a mix of assets that will deliver the highest possible return based on each client's risk tolerance. The firm also offers a variety of alternative investment options to enhance portfolio performance with more consistent returns and reduced volatility.Although the firm generally focuses on long-term investments, they may also seek to take advantage of opportunistic investments that are attractive given prevailing market conditions. They look for opportunities that: (1) possess strong absolute or relative return potential (2) have expected equity-like returns (at least 10% annualized) looking forward 6 to 18 months (3) represent a significant relative opportunity within a comparable asset class and (4) can be implemented with a mutual fund and/or ETF. Separate accounts or limited partnership mandates are only considered in appropriate situations.Evermay offers tax efficient investment options including ETFs, separately managed accounts and tax efficient market capture strategies. They also recommend high-grade, tax-exempt state and local bonds to help reduce a portfolios tax liability. The firm reviews all tax lots and assesses all tax implications prior to selling specific securities or executing trades. Evermay seeks to place less tax-efficient investments in tax-sheltered or tax-deferred accounts such as IRAs or SEP plans.




Website


http://www.evermaywealth.com





